# Core Frontend Standards

- Build with Next.js App Router and TypeScript.
- Use React functional components only.
- Style with Tailwind CSS; avoid CSS modules unless necessary.
- Prefer Next.js built-in features over custom alternatives.
- Keep implementations simple; do not over-engineer.
- Do not add unnecessary dependencies.
- Implement only requested scope; do not change unrelated code.
- Do not add backend, database, or API unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer static JSON data for MVP use cases.

# Code Quality

- Keep components small, reusable, and maintainable.
- Use clear, descriptive names.
- Remove unused code and avoid dead paths.
- Prefer composition over duplication.
- Prefer readability over cleverness.
